choices.text:
Put together a healthy meal plan for me for today.  I can't have dairy, garlic, honey, almonds, pistachios, or cashews
Sure! Here is a healthy meal plan that meets your dietary restrictions:
Breakfast: Scrambled eggs with spinach and tomatoes (no dairy) served with whole grain toast and orange juice. 
Lunch: Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens, cucumber, cherry tomatoes, and balsamic vinaigrette dressing (no garlic or honey). Served with quinoa and black beans for protein. 
Dinner: Baked salmon served with roasted sweet potato and asparagus (no almonds, pistachios, or cashews). Drizzle the salmon with olive oil and lemon juice for flavor.
